./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1535:A tradition's account of spiritual entry is best modeled as a compound grammar with four fields: what incapacity blocks ordinary entry, what minimum participation counts as real entry, what break mechanism is required if self-generated threshold entry is denied, and what residue policy governs claims after ordinary agency is negated. First-break type is not universal. It becomes an irreducible variable only in high-severity traditions that explicitly deny that any naturally self-generated threshold act can found the path.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1539:Neither source idea contained the full compound model. The First-Break Problem supplied entry mechanism and anthropology. Residual Burden supplied residue policy after negation. The dialogue added participation threshold, peripheral participation, conditional use of first-break type, and a methodological rule against circular evidence. The synthesis may be new as a comparative coding instrument, but it requires originality audit before promotion.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1552:The synthesis risks becoming too complex for the evidence. Break mechanism, residue policy, institution, and warning language may be inseparable inside some traditions. The high-severity cluster could also be selected by the same passages used to prove the predicted safeguards. Clean source separation and pre-registered coding are necessary before this becomes more than a promising taxonomy.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1577:- Pre-register coding rules for threshold acceptance, incapacity diagnosis, residue policy, institution, and break mechanism.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1579:- Test six cases: Theravada sangha entry, Confucian cultivation, Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian grace, Zen great doubt, and Dzogchen pointing-out.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1594:Self negating or self transcending paths do not simply require a minimum self, and they do not only differ by final residue. They organize a continuity ecology. Each path must preserve enough receptivity and reliability for transformation to occur, but that continuity can be internally managed, externally scaffolded, relationally entrusted, ritually stabilized, institutionally maintained, or theologically relocated. The path's dissolution target may pressure where continuity migrates, while its residue policy governs what may be authorized after negation. Practice ecology may either express that doctrinal pressure or precede it historically and force doctrine to explain an already existing arrangement.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1598:The source ideas separately named minimum self and residue policy. The dialogue produced a wider model that asks how receptivity, distributed continuity, authorized remainder, and practice ecology interact. Its possible novelty is not the claim that traditions differ about selfhood, but the testable causal question: whether what a path negates predicts where it stores continuity better than rival variables such as ritual form, institutional dependence, teacher authority, or devotional affect.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1603:- Codex idea 5a05c720a5039323: negative self practice differs by residue policy, meaning what a tradition authorizes to remain after negation.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1606:- Turn 3 Codex counter rebuttal: dissolution target, continuity distribution, residue policy, and practice ecology should be treated as interacting variables, with causal priority left open.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1607:- Shared textual pressure: SN 22.59, Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 through 6.16, Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, Dogen's Bendowa, Shinran's Tannisho and Kyogyoshinsho.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1613:The candidate risks becoming too elastic. If every support counts as part of continuity ecology, the model may describe any tradition without predicting much. Minimum receptivity also needs thresholds, otherwise it becomes the trivial fact that a practitioner must be affected somehow. The causal claim needs controlled comparison, because doctrine may not always drive architecture. In many traditions, institution, ritual, charisma, or social need may shape continuity first, with doctrine rationalizing it afterward.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1639:- Build a coding rubric with fields for dissolution target, minimum receptivity, internal capacities, external supports, residue policy, practice ecology, warning profile, verification method, and failure mode.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1706:- Code manuals, teacher instructions, adverse-event reports, and practitioner interviews across Theravada, Zen, Advaita, Dzogchen, Pure Land, Sufi, and Christian grace traditions.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1726:The source ideas already contained minimum-self architecture and custody-of-attention, but the dialogue created a distinct comparative object: the interface between assigned custody and practitioner receptivity. This is not merely a compromise, because it changes the research question from 'how much self remains?' or 'where does attention belong?' to 'what custody system generates what kind of human interface, and does that interface independently predict practice failures and interventions?' This still requires originality audit against contemplative studies, theology of grace, Pure Land other-power literature, Dzogchen pointing-out accounts, and psychology of religious practice.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1768:- Test Shin Buddhism, Christian infused contemplation, Dzogchen pointing-out, Theravada insight practice, and Advaita self-inquiry as initial cases.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1793:- Dialogue turn 1, Codex continuity-allocation challenge using Shinran and Other Power
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1828:- Test the model across Theravada insight, Advaita self-inquiry, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, Jodo Shinshu, and a Christian grace-centered contemplative tradition.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1907:Transformative traditions organize the beginning of practice through an interaction between what remains authorized after critique and how entry into transformation is narrated, enacted, or discovered. Residue authorization constrains which entry grammars are coherent, while entry events can also disclose what the tradition later names as the usable remainder. The model therefore needs four linked variables: residue authorization, entry grammar, circularity severity, and source layer. Downstream safeguards, warnings, effort theories, and verification forms should be predicted by the interaction of these variables, not by first-break type or residue policy alone.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1953:- Use paired comparisons where residue appears similar but entry differs, such as Dzogchen and Advaita, and where entry appears similar but residue differs, such as teacher encounter traditions with different anthropologies.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2040:- Codex, The Handoff Point Is The Variable: effort and gift should be coded by function, stage, support holder, credited source, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and repair.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2074:- Test paired traditions with shared context and different entry grammars: Zen and Jodo Shinshu, Calvinist and Wesleyan Christianity, Dzogchen and gradual-path Gelug.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2094:The source ideas held two different models: grain of capacity and residue policy. The dialogue created a developmental bridge between them. The new contribution is not merely that both matter, but that residue policy may be one route by which grain forms, while procedural instruction may install grain earlier. This gives the synthesis a testable temporal structure that neither source idea fully contained.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2100:- Dialogue turn 2: residue policy may become embodied grain through repeated practice under doctrinal and pedagogical framing.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2166:- Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Shinran's Tannisho, Dogen's Bendowa, The Cloud of Unknowing, and the Bahiya Sutta as candidate cases for different sites of direction.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2200:- Apply the layered rubric to Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Tannisho, Bendowa, Dzogchen pointing-out texts, and The Cloud of Unknowing.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2216:A contemplative path is shaped by three interacting factors: the operational capacities it requires, the residue policy it applies after negation, and the training ecology that calibrates those demands in lived practice. The operational profile names what must remain usable for the method to work, such as attention, memory, effort, reflexivity, receptivity, trust, or surrender. The residue policy names what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable. The practice ecology names the teacher, community, intensity, duration, screening, interpretation, and support conditions that determine whether the operational demand is stabilizing or destabilizing. This model predicts that safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns emerge from the interaction of all three, not from self-doctrine alone.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2220:The source ideas each had one main axis. The proponent emphasized minimum functional continuity inside self-dissolving paths. The challenger emphasized burden-of-proof rules after negation. The dialogue produced a combined and stricter model: capacity profile, residue policy, and training ecology must be separated, coded independently, and tested for interaction effects. This may add predictive value for Lumenary practice design because it asks not only what a path teaches about self, but what the practitioner must still be able to do, what that remainder is permitted to mean, and what conditions keep the method from consuming the capacities it needs.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2227:- Dialogue turn 2, Claude revision into capacity profile plus residue policy
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2240:The candidate synthesis may still overformalize living traditions. Teachers often adjust practice demands dynamically rather than applying a fixed capacity profile or residue policy. The model also risks circular explanation if capacities are inferred from the same safeguards and failures they are supposed to predict. Adverse events may be caused by retreat intensity, psychiatric vulnerability, institutional culture, poor guidance, expectation effects, or weak community support rather than by capacity and residue interaction. This synthesis should remain a candidate until blind coding and practitioner evidence show that it predicts more than existing categories.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2369:The candidate may still compress a messy causal ecology into one elegant frame. Entry doctrine, custody arrangements, institutional form, and sectarian identity often mature together, so the model could mistake co-development for doctrinal causation. Its key examples, such as Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu or Dzogchen versus gradual Tibetan paths, are promising but not clean controls. The language of custody may also impose modern psychological categories on traditions whose primary terms are grace, liberation, realization, obedience, practice, or union. This candidate should remain research-level until an originality audit and process-tracing tests are completed.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2397:- Use matched comparisons, especially Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu, Dzogchen versus gradual Tibetan sutra-path practice, and explicit grace traditions versus neighboring cooperation traditions.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2422:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2524:- Design a vignette study that codes teacher guidance across Jodo Shinshu, Theravada, Catholic spiritual direction, Dzogchen, recovery, and therapy settings.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2545:The familiar near-neighbor is Engler's claim that a person needs enough ego strength for self-observation and affect tolerance before no-self practice. The exact difference is that this model does not ask whether a healthy self is required in general. It splits the requirement into five capacities and tracks where each capacity is placed across stages of the path. Pudgalavada debates, Collins on selfless persons, Buddhist functional-self accounts, and contemporary self-pattern theory already make the Buddhist continuity problem hard to ignore. The exact difference is cross-tradition and architectural: the model predicts that effortful, other-power, direct-introduction, and practice-realization traditions will distribute receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration differently. The closest new pressure comes from Pure Land and Dzogchen. Instead of treating them as anomalies that need no self-capacity, the model predicts that they compress the capacity load into hearing, entrusting, recognition, teacher relation, and post-recognition stabilization. That graded relocation is the potentially original contribution, while the basic insight that self-dissolving practice needs functional capacities is strongly precedented.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2549:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power entrusting as a lens by refusing to assume that agency is the hidden engine of every path. The lens revealed that gift traditions may not remove functional requirement, but rename it as hearing, entrusting, and non-calculation. Its distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against right effort in SN 45.8.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2554:- Dogen practice-realization materials in notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md and prior local observations. Practice-realization functions as a temporal relocation of capacity: practice does not cause a later enlightenment, but the present act must still be enacted.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2561:The strongest counterexample is Jodo Shinshu itself. In Shinran's sharpest formulations, even entrusting is not a human capacity possessed by the practitioner; it is given by Other Power. Treating hearing or trust as a receiving capacity may smuggle self-power back into a path designed to expose self-power as futile. Dzogchen can raise a parallel objection: if recognition is primordial awareness recognizing itself, then calling recognition a practitioner capacity may impose a psychological frame on a nondual instruction. The thinking method also has a bias. Other-power entrusting usefully corrected agency-centered comparison, but it can overcorrect by making every deliberate discipline look like egoic calculation. Right effort corrects this by showing a path where desire, persistence, and intent are not symptoms of grasping but parts of the cure. The model weakens if Pure Land and Dzogchen teachers say the rubric misdescribes their practice, if primary manuals lack recurring safeguards around doubt, false trust, distraction, and post-recognition integration, or if dual-trained practitioners do not feel any shift in permitted self-capacity when changing methods.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2669:Self-dissolving practice does not simply require a self or erase a self. It creates a continuity ecology. Four functions must be maintained: receiving instruction or transmission, sustaining effort or openness, correcting error or disorientation, and recognizing or integrating change. Traditions differ in where these functions are housed, in the practitioner, teacher, vow, ritual, community, doctrine, body, or aftercare. Their post-gap report grammar is one way the ecology authorizes what happened, by privileging the subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, relation, or teacher recognition. Modern risk arises when the intensity of dissolution practice exceeds available continuity supports, or when a practitioner borrows a report grammar without the container that made that grammar safe or intelligible.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2720:- Blind-code Theravada vipassana, Advaita self-inquiry, Soto Zen, Dzogchen pointing-out, Pure Land nembutsu, Sufi dhikr, and trauma-informed mindfulness-based stress reduction.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2784:- Close-read Mahamudra or Dzogchen luminous-awareness instructions against Udana 1.10 and Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 to test whether luminosity is a fourth custody rule or an anomaly that breaks the map.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2810:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2991:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power as a lens by subtracting the assumption that every needed function must be owned by the practitioner. The method's distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against SN 45.8 on right effort.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2994:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3116:- Thinking method source: Dogen, Bendowa, practice and verification as one, summarized in Encyclopedia of Buddhism: https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3127:The model can romanticize distance and make real suffering, ignorance, or alienation look useful. A Buddhist gradual path may say distance is not a noble instrument but a condition to end through training. A Zen enactment path may say treating no-distance as a function already misses practice-realization. A Sufi may say longing is not a psychological tool but the trace of a real Beloved. The Dogen lens used here may bias the comparison against causal paths by making sequence look like delusion; the mindfulness lens may over-neutralize devotion by turning longing into an observed state. The idea should be weakened unless close practice texts show that each path deliberately trains with its distance policy.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3240:The boundary between effort and gift is best treated as a timed transfer, not a fixed scale. A path may train receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration, then tell the practitioner that the very capacity just trained cannot be owned by the ordinary self. Effort paths keep cultivation visible until ownership is stripped from what was cultivated. Other-power paths move the transfer to the entrance: hearing, saying, and entrusting remain visible, but calculation is forbidden from the start. Direct-introduction paths remove production at the recognition point, then require stabilization, conduct, and guidance after recognition. Practice-realization collapses transfer into the act itself: practice is not a bridge to later gain, but it must still be enacted. The useful rubric is therefore not effort versus gift. It is function, stage, support holder, credited source, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and repair when the transfer fails.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3251:- Dogen practice-realization source: St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology on Dogen, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Buddhism/Dogen. Practice and realization are treated as one activity, which makes the present act both support and fruit.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3254:- Near-neighbor pressure: Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO. Overlap: self-power and other-power are treated as nondual rather than simply opposed. Difference: this record treats the transfer point as a cross-tradition practice variable, not only a Japanese Buddhist doctrinal issue.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3285:- Build the rubric as a coding sheet with these fields: capacity, stage, support holder, credited source, forbidden claimant, transfer instruction, safeguard, failure mode, and repair practice.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3437:- Dogen's oneness of practice-verification, summarized at https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen, for the claim that realization is not something to expect outside practice.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3491:This is distinct from residue policy, inferential gap, alarm profile, verification architecture, and stopping rule. Those name remainder, conclusion, danger, proof, and halted inquiry. The protected-variable model names the value or function each tradition keeps invariant across those layers. It predicts that apparent convergence is safest where protected variables overlap, and most generative where they clash.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3614:A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3659:- Ask Jodo Shinshu and Dzogchen teachers whether register-sensitive interface mapping avoids self-power or psychological distortion, or whether even this second-order mapping remains misleading.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3661:- Test whether the model predicts warning profiles in manuals before reading their warnings. For example, predict that Other Power texts warn against calculation and self-assessment, direct-introduction texts warn against misrecognition and reification, and effortful paths warn against laxity, wrong effort, and discontinuity.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3815:The synthesis may become too elaborate to compress the phenomena it studies. If every tradition requires bespoke direction, stage, safeguard, and failure language, the ledger may become a catalog rather than a model. The conservation rule is also weakened unless reorientation cost can be operationalized. Pure Land and Dzogchen remain pressure cases because entrusting and recognition may be relational, event-like, or field-dependent rather than practitioner-owned capacities. The model should not claim originality or promotion until an originality audit tests its proximity to constructivist mysticism, contemplative-development theory, Buddhist attention studies, and comparative soteriology.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4001:The model may over-systematize traditions that intentionally resist clean endings. Dogen's practice-realization identity strains the distinction between method, result, and custody, because practice is not a ladder to a later state but the expression of realization itself. Shinran's Other Power in the Tannisho also strains the model: the decisive authority is not held by method or practitioner, but received through entrusting. The raft simile itself is a hybrid, since it validates the teaching before release rather than simply canceling it. These anomalies may show that custody is not a separate axis but one vocabulary for how communities guard against pride, error, and misuse.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4146:- Prediction: Hybrid texts such as the Heart Sutra, Dogen's practice-realization writings, MN 22, and the Tannisho should show explicit boundary management around trust, release, embodiment, or received authority. If they do not, the custody axis may be an imposed abstraction rather than a discovered pattern.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4156:- Close-read Dogen, Shinran, Dionysius, Eckhart, Nagarjuna, the Mandukya, MN 22, and koan curricula for explicit boundary markers: when to trust, release, deny, embody, or submit a method to communal judgment.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4171:A practice is not complete when it gives a person an experience. It is complete only when it teaches the person how to return. The live question has two parts: does the method let the result stand, or does it undermine every claim to have a result; and after the result, is the method kept, set down, or carried as conduct? The Mandukya leans toward a result that can be known. The Heart Sutra undermines attainment while still retaining reliance. MN 22 validates right use and then warns against carrying the raft. Rinzai koan work can exhaust ordinary thinking while remaining a formal curriculum. Dogen strains the whole sequence by making practice and realization one. The practical danger is not only false insight. It is turning a method into proof of worth, or abandoning it before it has trained ordinary conduct.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4184:- Dogen Uji source card and prior Bendowa practice-realization anomaly in local observations. Used as pressure against any model that assumes a clean before and after.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4193:The model may still be a modern sorting tool placed over traditions that would reject the frame. Dogen's practice-realization identity is the hardest anomaly: if practice and realization are one, then asking what happens after completion may already distort the source. Tannisho-style Other Power and inherited communal religion would also strain the model because the practitioner may not own the decisive method at all. A second weakness is prior art: Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Katz, Hori, and VCE-style research already show that practice, authority, worldview, institution, and interpretation shape religious experience. The model should be weakened if split-source coding cannot predict held-out warnings or re-entry rules better than institution type, teacher style, tradition label, or ordinary social authority.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4249:The three-box completion model was weakened by MN 22, Heart Sutra reliance, Rinzai curriculum, Dogen practice-realization, authority-boundary prior art, and modern perfectionism and burnout pressure. The surviving teaching is narrower: test the return, not the peak.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4324:- Next action: Create a code sheet and test Mandukya Advaita, Heart Sutra, MN 22, Rinzai koan training, Dogen, Tannisho, Dionysius, and one Sufi source with held-out warning passages.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4361:- Close-read Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius, one Dzogchen pointing-out manual, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising confidence.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4380:The closest prior argument is local becoming in relativity: Stein, Arthur, Dieks, and Savitt already treat proper time, light cones, and causal diamonds as ways to avoid a single global present. The distinct move is not to claim a new physics of time. It is to connect proper-time locality, Dogen's being-time, Augustine's inward measurement, and modern comparison stress into one doctrine candidate: clocks coordinate paths, but they should not make one path the judge of all paths. Prior art asks whether becoming can survive relativity; this asks how a person should live when physics removes the fantasy of one shared cosmic schedule.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4392:- Primary contemplative comparison: Dogen, Shobogenzo Uji, refuses separation between being and time and warns against treating time as merely flying away; notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4394:- Practitioner-method source: Augustine's inward observation was used as the first lens, watching how memory, attention, and expectation make duration legible. Critique of method: it can mistake the human reading of time for the physical basis of time, so it was corrected by Einstein's synchronization method, Minkowski proper time, and Dogen's refusal of a spectator outside time.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4399:The strongest objection is that the idea may be local becoming with spiritual and therapeutic clothing. Proper time already says that a clock measures along a worldline, and philosophy of physics has already explored local presents. Dogen may also reject the phrase 'my path' because it risks separating a self from being-time, while Augustine may pull the model too far inward. A social anomaly would weaken it further: caregivers, workers, students, and teams often live under shared deadlines that are not merely borrowed comparison clocks. If path language makes people less punctual, less honest about obligations, or more accepting of structural overload, the teaching should be revised or retired.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4455:Survived close reading of Einstein's clock synchronization, Minkowski proper time, Augustine's inward measurement, Dogen's no-separation, Plotinus on eternity and succession, and prior-art pressure from local becoming in relativity.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4553:### Dogen No-Separation Pressure
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4578:- Close-read Dogen Uji against Stein, Dieks, and Arthur. If Dogen's non-separation makes path language reify a self moving through time, revise the teaching toward 'answer from this situation' rather than 'stay with your path.'
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4592:When a clock works, it has not answered what time is. It has made one relation shareable: this event, this body, this signal, and this record can be compared. The felt present is not a private hallucination inside a finished block, and it is not a magical slice that alone exists. It is the place where relations become answerable to action. In that place a promise can be kept, a message can be sent, a body can rest, and a mistake can be repaired. Physics gives the external half through synchronization, proper time, and relational observables. Augustine gives the inward half through memory, attention, and expectation. Dogen gives the refusal to place the person outside time as a spectator. The crux is method authority: clocks can authorize coordination without authorizing a final metaphysics of flow, block, or self.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4596:The nearest neighbors already deny that clocks measure a substance called time. Relational time, emergent clock-time, and Dogen-block-universe comparisons all reach parts of the claim. The exact difference is narrower: a successful timing method should be trusted for coordination but refused as a ruler over metaphysics or personal worth. Existing prior art asks what time is, whether all moments exist, or how clock-time can be reconstructed. This finding asks what a working method is allowed to authorize, then ties that limit to a modern wound: people letting schedules and future projections act as verdicts on the self.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4606:- Primary contemplative comparison: Dogen, Shobogenzo Uji source card notes that being and time are not separate and that time should not be treated as merely flying away; notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4607:- Primary-text close reading: Einstein makes time shareable by synchronization between clocks; Augustine finds measurable duration in expectation, attention, and memory; Dogen refuses the spectator who stands outside time. The comparison reveals three different authorizations: coordination, inward measurement, and non-separation.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4668:Survived primary comparison between Einstein's operational clock, Augustine's inward measurement, and Dogen's refusal to stand outside time; also survived prior-art pressure from relational and emergent time by narrowing to method authority.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4772:- Next action: Close-read MMK chapter 19 against Augustine Confessions XI and Dogen Uji.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4817:This idea could smuggle institutional authority back into spiritual life under the friendly word correction. Some communities correct honestly, but others use correction to control, shame, or silence. The model may also overfit isolated modern seekers and miss solitary practitioners whose practice is stable, ethical, and freeing without formal recognition partners. Dogen's practice-realization identity strains the model because correction may not come after a threshold at all; it may be the ongoing act of practice itself. Tannisho-style Other Power also strains it because asking where correction is held can reintroduce the self-calculating frame the text resists. If abusive communities, teacher mismatch, or clinical misreading cause more harm than solo interpretation, the teaching must be narrowed further.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4977:- Next action: Build a small codebook using Mandukya, MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen, Tannisho, Dionysius, Rinzai koan sources, and one contemplative science safety source.
