./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:11:The family of models built around this frontier shares one move that should now be challenged: the claim that continuity, custody, or support is always held somewhere, and that what a path negates predicts where it migrates. This move quietly fuses two different claims. The first is constitutive and trivially true: a transforming person is always sustained by some body, habit, teacher, text, vow, or community, so support can always be found 'relocated' after the fact. This half is inherited from extended-mind reasoning and predicts nothing, because no possible case can contradict it. The second is differential and worth testing: what a path negates predicts where support migrates and how it fails. Only the differential half is a finding, and it has purchase only where a search-and-negation sequence actually runs. In search-refusing paths, where the seeking that generates remainder pressure is itself forbidden (Huangbo), denied a before-and-after (Dogen), or replaced by direct recognition (Dzogchen), there is no remainder to locate; redescribing those traditions' teachers, vows, and communities as 'relocated continuity' is not a confirmation of the model but the visible symptom of its unfalsifiability. Lumenary should therefore narrow the whole continuity-and-remainder apparatus to search-sequence paths, separate the constitutive claim from the differential claim in every record, and refuse to count a model as confirmed unless it names an observation that would show it false in a specific case.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:15:The frontier has repeatedly listed Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen as anomalies, but each prior model absorbs them by saying the support simply moved to teacher, vow, or present act. The new move is to treat that absorption itself as the diagnostic failure rather than a successful extension: a model whose central concept can swallow every counterexample has stopped doing work. The specific contribution is to name the inherited source of that generosity (extended-mind constitutivity), to separate the trivially true claim from the testable one, and to restrict the testable claim to paths that actually run the negation sequence. This is a falsifiability critique of a model family, not another variable added to it, which is what distinguishes it from the recent question-permission and support-holder findings it otherwise agrees with.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:19:- Run mode: Critique. The active frontier (remainder pressure and continuity after self-negation) is saturated with near-duplicate models, so this run pressures the family rather than adding another member.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:20:- Primary-text comparison: SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta runs an explicit search-and-negation sequence through the five aggregates and ends in non-clinging, which leaves a live question of what carries non-clinging afterward (https://suttacentral.net/sn22.59/en/bodhi). Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, forbids the seeking mind itself, so no downstream remainder is produced to be located (https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236). The comparison reveals that 'remainder pressure' is generated by the search sequence, not by self-negation as such.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:21:- Supporting anomaly text: Dogen, Bendowa, treats practice and realization as one act, so there is no 'after negation' interval in which continuity must be re-housed (notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md).
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:30:The critique may prove too much. Almost every rich interpretive framework looks unfalsifiable from outside, and the frontier brief itself asks that this work remain a comparative and practitioner-facing heuristic, not a predictive science; demanding a prohibited observation may impose a natural-science standard where it does not belong. A second strain: the differential claim might retain purchase even in search-refusing paths, because those paths show their own characteristic failures (Pure Land warnings against self-power calculation, Dzogchen warnings against reifying recognition). If those failures cluster predictably with what each path refuses, then a support-and-failure frame earns predictive status there too, and my scope-restriction to search-sequence paths is weakened. A third strain: this critique is itself close to Lumenary's own progress-gate and duplicate-production findings, so its novelty is partly recursive, and it should be scored modestly.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:56:Tags: falsifiability, spiritual-bypass, loneliness, meaning-loss, self-negation, critique-mode
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:80:Survives the search-refusing anomalies (Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen) and the extended-mind near-neighbor by separating what is always true from what tells you about your own case.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:162:- Prediction: If remainder pressure and continuity-location are genuinely sequence-dependent, then search-refusing paths (Huangbo, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct recognition, Pure Land) should not yield a differentiated, predictable map of where support is held and how it fails; their warnings should instead be about refusing the search itself. If blind coding shows these paths produce stable, differentiated support-and-failure clusters tied to what they refuse, the scope-restriction is weakened and the differential claim survives outside search-sequence paths.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:165:- Next action: Build a small codebook separating refused-search warnings from continuity-location warnings, then blind-code Huangbo, Bendowa, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and Tannisho.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:191:- If remainder pressure is produced by the search sequence rather than by self-negation as such, then practitioners moved from a search-and-negation method into a search-refusing method should report the felt question 'what remains / what holds this' fading rather than relocating. If the question persists unchanged across the switch, the sequence-dependence claim is weakened.
./runs/20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/output.md:192:- Test the scope-restriction directly: code Huangbo, Dogen, and Dzogchen sources for whether their warnings and failures cluster predictably with what each path refuses. If they do, the differential claim has purchase even without a search sequence, and the restriction must be relaxed.
