./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1522:- Treat Dogen, Shankara, and Dzogchen as boundary cases unless a source-specific claimant grammar shows that credit language is admissible.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1537:A tradition's account of spiritual entry is best modeled as a compound grammar with four fields: what incapacity blocks ordinary entry, what minimum participation counts as real entry, what break mechanism is required if self-generated threshold entry is denied, and what residue policy governs claims after ordinary agency is negated. First-break type is not universal. It becomes an irreducible variable only in high-severity traditions that explicitly deny that any naturally self-generated threshold act can found the path.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1541:Neither source idea contained the full compound model. The First-Break Problem supplied entry mechanism and anthropology. Residual Burden supplied residue policy after negation. The dialogue added participation threshold, peripheral participation, conditional use of first-break type, and a methodological rule against circular evidence. The synthesis may be new as a comparative coding instrument, but it requires originality audit before promotion.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1554:The synthesis risks becoming too complex for the evidence. Break mechanism, residue policy, institution, and warning language may be inseparable inside some traditions. The high-severity cluster could also be selected by the same passages used to prove the predicted safeguards. Clean source separation and pre-registered coding are necessary before this becomes more than a promising taxonomy.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1579:- Pre-register coding rules for threshold acceptance, incapacity diagnosis, residue policy, institution, and break mechanism.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1581:- Test six cases: Theravada sangha entry, Confucian cultivation, Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian grace, Zen great doubt, and Dzogchen pointing-out.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1596:Self negating or self transcending paths do not simply require a minimum self, and they do not only differ by final residue. They organize a continuity ecology. Each path must preserve enough receptivity and reliability for transformation to occur, but that continuity can be internally managed, externally scaffolded, relationally entrusted, ritually stabilized, institutionally maintained, or theologically relocated. The path's dissolution target may pressure where continuity migrates, while its residue policy governs what may be authorized after negation. Practice ecology may either express that doctrinal pressure or precede it historically and force doctrine to explain an already existing arrangement.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1600:The source ideas separately named minimum self and residue policy. The dialogue produced a wider model that asks how receptivity, distributed continuity, authorized remainder, and practice ecology interact. Its possible novelty is not the claim that traditions differ about selfhood, but the testable causal question: whether what a path negates predicts where it stores continuity better than rival variables such as ritual form, institutional dependence, teacher authority, or devotional affect.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1605:- Codex idea 5a05c720a5039323: negative self practice differs by residue policy, meaning what a tradition authorizes to remain after negation.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1608:- Turn 3 Codex counter rebuttal: dissolution target, continuity distribution, residue policy, and practice ecology should be treated as interacting variables, with causal priority left open.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1609:- Shared textual pressure: SN 22.59, Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 through 6.16, Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, Dogen's Bendowa, Shinran's Tannisho and Kyogyoshinsho.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1615:The candidate risks becoming too elastic. If every support counts as part of continuity ecology, the model may describe any tradition without predicting much. Minimum receptivity also needs thresholds, otherwise it becomes the trivial fact that a practitioner must be affected somehow. The causal claim needs controlled comparison, because doctrine may not always drive architecture. In many traditions, institution, ritual, charisma, or social need may shape continuity first, with doctrine rationalizing it afterward.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1641:- Build a coding rubric with fields for dissolution target, minimum receptivity, internal capacities, external supports, residue policy, practice ecology, warning profile, verification method, and failure mode.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1708:- Code manuals, teacher instructions, adverse-event reports, and practitioner interviews across Theravada, Zen, Advaita, Dzogchen, Pure Land, Sufi, and Christian grace traditions.
./runs/20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1728:The source ideas already contained minimum-self architecture and custody-of-attention, but the dialogue created a distinct comparative object: the interface between assigned custody and practitioner receptivity. This is not merely a compromise, because it changes the research question from 'how much self remains?' or 'where does attention belong?' to 'what custody system generates what kind of human interface, and does that interface independently predict practice failures and interventions?' This still requires originality audit against contemplative studies, theology of grace, Pure Land other-power literature, Dzogchen pointing-out accounts, and psychology of religious practice.
